The Band:
Caitlin Merison - Lead vocals and guitar
Benjamin Davis - Lead guitar and backing vocals
Iain Cobby - Bass, keyboards and backing vocals
Sol Buckner - Rhythm guitar and backing vocals

The band was originally formed in February 2014. Listed in the Beatles Day 15 programme by Sol Buckner as 'Caitlin and Friends'. The early line up were joined in late February 2014 by an experienced bass player Dave Hobbs who agreed to help out for Beatles Day. At the same time a talented young guitarist Benjamin Davis joined the line up as Lead Guitarist.

After just a few weeks of rehearsals the band finally decided on the band name 'Mania'. The band made their debut performance at 'Beatles Day 15' on 6th April 2014 at the White Rock Theatre, Hastings, East Sussex. UK.

Post the 'Bealtes Day 15' event their bass guitarist and keyboard player, Iain Cobby, completed the line-up. 

Mania are currently building their repertoire and have performed throughout 2014 and 2015 at various charity and local fund raising events including Hastings Beatles Day, Hastings Pirate Day, Charity for Kids, Action Aid and Hastings Half Marathon.

War Widows' Stories raises awareness of the lives of war widows in Britain past and present. On SoundCloud, we share the interviews we have recorded thus far, and you can find the full transcripts and more information about the history of war widowhood in Britain on our website. 

The project is led by Dr Nadine Muller (Liverpool John Moores University) and Dr Ailbhe McDaid (University of Liverpool). We work in partnership with the War Widows' Association of Great Britain, and the first year of the project has been supported by a Sharing Heritage grant from the Heritage Lottery Fund. 

We welcome enquiries from members of the public, prospective volunteers, the media, academics, and anyone working with the armed forces or related charities and governments departments.

I didn't choose what I am. In the whole creation, I just spread my sin. The real essence of humanity.

8FUL STRIKE was born in 2008 in Padua from 7 musicians coming from different bands and backgrounds, but with the same aim: to create a new project, a new band to mix all their different influences and their will to shock the audience from every point of view. Their idea of a metal band is a synergy of intents, music, inspiration and visual impact.

Influenced by modern bands from the NWOAHM, with adds from the HC world and a taste of old school shit, they created their own style and will spread it with strenght, granting every time so a powerful live show, full of energy, motion, anger and hate, that you won’t be able to ignore it!

The 7 musicians started performing in the North-East of Italy, sharing the stage with many important bands of the local scene and taking part in different contests. 2 years of live shows brang them to the attention of different recording labels and in 2010 they finally reached an agreement with JetGlow Recordings.

In November 2010 they will release they first LP “Leave Yourself Behind”,under JetGlow Recordings. The album will be the result of more than two years of hard work and sacrifices and from the very first moment it will share with you the 8fulstrike essence.

In 2011 the band continued spreading their first studio piece touring in Italy and Switzerland, advertising it in many radio programs and magazines, with good answers from the critics.

In 2012 the band, with the support of friends, radios and other bands, decided to promote a campaign in favor of underground music to help the scene in growing and improving.
They also keep gigs going and are ready for their first videoclip, followed by the second full lenght album.

In summer 2012, they win the JoRock Contest 2012 and reach the 3rd place at AltichieRock

8FULSTRIKE...Stay tuned, the hate never gives up...

Keine Standard Tattoos vom Handgelenk bis zur Schulter, kein obligatorischer Moshpart, keine Testosteronwolke, keine Lust über Musikrichtungen zu philosophieren, keine Szene.
Deadly Habit spielen sich seit 2014 die Finger wund. HC-Punkrock heißt es bei den vier Berlinern, ohne großen Schnickschnack. Schnell nach vorne, hier und da melodisch aber Hauptsache hinterher ist die Stimme heiser. Oder schon vorher. Und dazwischen. 
Die erste EP „Deadly Habit“ erschien April 2014 und ist voll mit genau diesem Punkrock, der auch heimliche Hardcore Einflüsse durchscheinen lässt. Seit der EP ging`s rund in den berüchtigten Kellern Berlins, wo Deadly Habit Größen wie Shemale Trouble, Disturbance, Bottlekids, No Fun at All und Satanic Surfers supporten konnten. Mit der neuen EP „The Rule of Ignorance“ (April 2020) geht es wieder rein in den Tourbus und raus aus der Hauptstadt. 'Deadly Habit' trinken aus und legen los. Man sieht sich.
